column5: I'm going here later today, Any advice would be appreciated. Information (locations and species) also wanted.
I live right around the corner, drop by for a cold one.  Just pull up to the Timmy's and wave, I'll be right there.
Right now is there any action in centennial a park pond.
Lots of catfish, I got a few bites but none landed unfortunately.
You should of tried trolling for them.Better hooksets.
I don't have a boat and this is a small pond.
Every learning Angler has to have one of these.  http://www.trollingbobber.com/
Yeah i doubt catfish were biting, they just inhale any bait they find SLURP. You're lucky to get a lip hookset, usually they will gut hook themselves if they could.
Some people beside me were catching only catfish every few minutes.
I'm not so sure it's only the Catfish that are biting....  Seems rather slow with the questions all of a sudden.
I'm pretty sure it was catfish because some people beside me were only catching catfish and using the same bait as me , worms.
Contributing to the delinquincy of minor eh Doug?
I think you meant to reply to douG not me. right?
people beside me were using the same rig as i changed mine after I saw their's.
